title: "ModelMesh Data Flow - Generated by Claude Opus 4.6"
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client / Controller
    participant MM1 as ModelMesh Pod (Receiving)<br/>8033/TCP gRPC<br/>Optional TLS/mTLS
    participant etcd as etcd Cluster<br/>2379/TCP gRPC<br/>TLS + Certificate Auth
    participant MM2 as ModelMesh Pod (Target)<br/>8080/TCP Thrift/litelinks<br/>Optional TLS/mTLS
    participant Runtime as Model Runtime<br/>8085/TCP or UDS gRPC<br/>plaintext

    Note over Client,Runtime: Flow 1: Model Inference Request

    Client->>MM1: gRPC inference request<br/>Port 8033/TCP<br/>Optional TLS/mTLS
    MM1->>etcd: Lookup model location<br/>Port 2379/TCP<br/>TLS + Certificate Auth

    alt Model loaded locally
        MM1->>Runtime: Forward inference<br/>Port 8085/TCP or UDS<br/>gRPC plaintext
        Runtime-->>MM1: Inference result
    else Model on another pod
        MM1->>MM2: Forward request<br/>Port 8080/TCP<br/>Thrift/litelinks<br/>Optional TLS
        MM2->>Runtime: Forward inference<br/>Port 8085/TCP or UDS<br/>gRPC plaintext
        Runtime-->>MM2: Inference result
        MM2-->>MM1: Response via litelinks
    end

    MM1-->>Client: gRPC inference response<br/>Optional TLS

    Note over Client,Runtime: Flow 2: Model Registration and Loading

    Client->>MM1: registerModel RPC<br/>Port 8033/TCP gRPC<br/>Optional TLS/mTLS
    MM1->>etcd: Store model record<br/>Port 2379/TCP TLS
    MM1->>MM2: Place model (leader decision)<br/>Port 8080/TCP Thrift<br/>Optional TLS
    MM2->>Runtime: loadModel RPC<br/>Port 8085/TCP or UDS<br/>gRPC plaintext
    Runtime-->>MM2: Model loaded confirmation

    Note over Client,Runtime: Flow 3: Prometheus Metrics Scraping

    participant Prom as Prometheus Scraper

    Prom->>MM1: GET /metrics<br/>Port 2112/TCP<br/>HTTPS (self-signed TLS)
    MM1-->>Prom: Prometheus metrics response
